            [title] => SimpleXMLElement Object
                (
                    [0] => 6 Places in Malta serving up Tasty Cocktails
                )

            [date] => SimpleXMLElement Object
                (
                    [0] => 2017-07-07 05:33:46
                )

            [content] => <span style="font-weight:400;">Nothing says ‘summer in Malta’ like sipping gorgeous cocktails by the sea as a laid-back afternoon turns into a sultry Mediterranean night. With so many great places to try dotted all over the island, we thought we’d give you a few tips on where to get started when you’re in the mood for a cheeky cocktail (or three). </span>
<h2><b>1 | The Black Sheep, Sliema</b></h2>
<b>https://www.facebook.com/theStrand72/</b>

<span style="font-weight:400;">Just across the road from the buzzing Sliema seafront, you’ll find The Black Sheep - a cute little lounge serving up some great food and drinks to the hungry (and thirsty) masses. Oh, did we mention the happy hour? </span>

https://www.instagram.com/p/BVzn2rBhttU/?taken-at=365324153810780


<h2><b>2 | Hugo’s Lounge, Paceville</b></h2>
<b>https://www.facebook.com/Hugosloungemalta/</b>

<span style="font-weight:400;">If you’re looking to be right in the heart of Malta’s entertainment district for a night of stunning drinks and a bit of dancing, then look no further than Hugo’s Lounge in Paceville. There’s a happy hour, delicious Asian cuisine, and sumptuous platters - what else could you possibly need? </span>

https://www.instagram.com/p/BWKTwdJjbWf/?taken-by=hugosloungemalta


<h2><b>3 | StrEat Whisky Bar amp; Bistro, Valletta</b></h2>
<b>https://www.facebook.com/streatwhisky/</b>

<span style="font-weight:400;">Our stunning capital city is the perfect backdrop to any drinks-date, day or night! Check out StrEat in bustling Strait Street for some divine cocktails and a fully-stocked whisky bar just waiting to be sampled.</span>

https://www.instagram.com/p/BSKEisXAsno/?taken-by=streatwhisky


<h2><b>4 | Cafe’ Society, Valletta</b></h2>
<b>https://www.facebook.com/cafesocietyuptown/</b>

<span style="font-weight:400;">Another little gem located in one of Valletta’s many side streets, Cafe’ Society offers its patrons a refreshing alternative to your typical bars and lounges. The best way to enjoy your ice-cold cocktail is to grab a chair (or comfy cushion) and sit yourself out on the smooth, well-worn steps outside! </span>

https://www.instagram.com/p/BVuzIvXFLim/?taken-by=cafesocietyvalletta1


<h2><b>5 | Zion Reggae Bar, Marsaskala </b></h2>
<b>https://www.facebook.com/zionmalta/</b>

<span style="font-weight:400;">Venture down to Malta’s idyllic south for something different at Zion, a chilled out bar complete with delicious cocktails, yummy food, and a beautiful sea view. </span>

https://www.instagram.com/p/BVC5Ti3jI2v/?taken-by=zionreggaebar


<h2><b>6 | The Thirsty Barber, Paceville </b></h2>
<b>https://www.facebook.com/thethirstybarber/</b>

<span style="font-weight:400;">Hidden behind a vintage-style phone booth in Paceville, you’ll find the entrance to Malta’s first ever prohibition-era bar - The Thirsty Barber. A visit to this beautiful bar will be rewarded with some of the most over-the-top cocktails you’ve ever seen, and a classy night out you won’t forget any time soon - unless you order too many of those pretty drinks! </span>

https://www.instagram.com/p/BVSk7htDtzs/?taken-by=thethirstybarber
