            [content] => No matter how hard we may try to listen to our well-meaning dentists and avoid the more sugary things in life, sometimes you just need to satisfy that craving. Whether you’re a serial candy-bandit or just want to treat yourself to something tasty, we’ve got a few places to get you started on your next sugar run.
<h2><b>1 | Flora’s, Naxxar</b></h2>
https://www.facebook.com/florascafemalta/

This cute cafe is a pastel-coloured dream filled with all the sweet treats and comforting cups to tea you could possibly want. Oh, one more thing - it’s all home-made, and the only thing sweeter than the cupcakes is the fantastic service!

https://www.instagram.com/p/BSb6kQKjZNu/?taken-by=florastearoom
<h2><b>2 | Miss Ellen’s Travelling Treats</b></h2>
https://www.facebook.com/MissEllensMalta/

Miss Ellen’s is Malta’s first ever retro sweet shop, and comes complete with an adorable mint-green vintage van that drives around some of the island’s busiest towns to bring old school sweets and chocolates to the masses.

https://www.instagram.com/p/BU4MQC_FOXL/?taken-by=missellens_
<h2><b>3 | Molly’s, Mosta</b></h2>
https://www.facebook.com/mollysartcafe/

For some of the fluffiest pancakes on the island, hit Molly’s in Constitution Street, Mosta, and leave the tight pants at home! Yes, we would like some extra <i>panna</i> please.

https://www.instagram.com/p/BP5UQEIgcWB/?taken-by=mollys_cafe
<h2><b>4 | Busy Bee, Msida</b></h2>
https://www.facebook.com/busybeemalta/

This classy little cafe has been a local favourite ever since opening its doors in 1933. Here, you’ll be spoilt for choice with all those time-honoured classics - cannoli, chocolate eclairs, almond pastries, <i>ottijiet, </i>ice-creams, and much more. Our top tip? Try and grab a table near the big window for the perfect people-watching position.

https://www.instagram.com/p/BWcxZ7lAAKN/?taken-by=busybeemalta
<h2><b>5 | Waffle Bros, Msida</b></h2>
https://www.facebook.com/WaffleBros.be/?ref=br_rs

A relatively new addition to the busy town, Waffle Bros has already become something of an institution among Maltesers. Build your own delicious waffle or chomp on some churros - and don’t forget to wash it all down with a cup of their fantastic coffee.

https://www.instagram.com/p/BW5J2Afl3aL/?taken-by=wafflebrosmalta_taxbiex


<h2><b>6 | Shoreditch, Paceville</b></h2>
https://www.facebook.com/shoreditchmalta/

Located right in the heart of Paceville, Shoreditch is the place to be if you’re looking to take your pancake game to the next level - and we mean the next level.

https://www.instagram.com/p/BWkxYwJD2G0/?taken-by=shoreditch_malta
