            [title] => SimpleXMLElement Object
                (
                    [0] => 5 ways to celebrate Halloween in Malta
                )

            [date] => SimpleXMLElement Object
                (
                    [0] => 2017-10-18 10:00:39
                )

            [content] => Malta, being the Roman Catholic country that it is, has never been big on celebrating Halloween. However, this predominantly American holiday is growing in popularity in our islands as the years go by, and is enjoyed by children and adults alike.

<img class=" aligncenter" src="https://media.giphy.com/media/l3vRfhFD8hJCiP0uQ/giphy.gif" alt=" dancing halloween pumpkin dance the pumpkin dance GIF" />
<h3><strong>1. Go on the <a href="https://www.funmalta.com/valletta-ghost-tour" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Valletta Ghost Tour</a></strong></h3>
As you may or may not know, Valletta has a LOT of history. From The Great Siege of 1565, to both World Wars, it is safe to say that if ghosts were in fact real, they’d all be hanging out at Cafe’ Cordina, waiting to “BOO” you during the Valletta Ghost Tour. Apart from visiting Valletta in all its nightly glory, you’ll be able to learn all about the ghosts which inhabit the area- almost transported in time! Book through Fun Malta- follow this link right here for more information: <a href="https://www.funmalta.com/valletta-ghost-tour" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.funmalta.com/valletta-ghost-tour</a>

<img class=" aligncenter" src="https://media3.giphy.com/media/Z8pzh8afGbZle/giphy.gif" alt=" animated halloween cartoon ghost scooby doo GIF" />
<h3><strong>2. Dress up as Fundamentally Maltese Characters</strong></h3>
What’s stopping you from dressing up as your favourite Maltese personalities? From La Vallette to your mother-in-law, the choices are truly endless. Some good couple costume ideas are the Maltese Flag, the Azure Window (R.I.P), and possibly twistees and kinnie. Extra points for dressing up as pastizzi.

<img class=" aligncenter" src="https://media.giphy.com/media/xT9KVeCUuPX8ELnbl6/giphy.gif" alt=" halloween mean girls lindsay lohan mean girls movie cady heron GIF" />
<h3><strong>3. Go Trick or Treating</strong></h3>
So once you’ve decided on your costume, it’s time to show everyone what a truly Malta-loving trick or treater you are. Major areas to hit may be Sliema, St. Julians and Swieqi area, where lots of children and teens alike attempt trick or treating. Whether you trick or receive a treat, it’s great fun!

<img class=" aligncenter" src="https://media.giphy.com/media/VqrAsdR88b9VC/giphy.gif" alt="DogVacay halloween puppies funny dog cute puppy GIF" />
<h3><strong>4. Watch a scary movie</strong></h3>
What’s better than movie theatre popcorn, candy, and a screamer? Go to the Eden Cinemas on halloween night- there are many horror movies out right now, as tis’ the season to be absolutely terrified! From Stephen King’s  “IT” to the notoriously creepy “Mother” (not even Jennifer Lawrence can make this film less horrifying), the seat jumping in guaranteed.

<img class=" aligncenter" src="https://media.giphy.com/media/s4Q3geM5T1XCo/giphy.gif" alt=" horror creepy scary it clown GIF" />
<h3><strong>5. Make these cute Rice Krispy Treat Brains to gross out your friends and family</strong></h3>
[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="650"]<img src="https://leftbraincraftbrain.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Rice-Krispy-Treat-Brains-Square-Left-Brain-Craft-Brain.png" alt="Image result for rice krispy treats brains" width="650" height="650" /> <i><span style="font-weight:400;">Via Left Brain Craft Brain</span></i>[/caption]

These are a no-brainer (get it?); they are so simple to make! All you will need is 6 cups of Rice Krispies Cereal, red food colouring, red gel icing some cooking spray, 3 tablespoons of butter and a bag of mini marshmallows. Melt the butter, add marshmallows and heat until melted, adding the red food colouring as you stir. Add the cereal and stir into the gooey mush, and once all cereals are evenly coated, spray hands with cooking spray and shape the cereal mush into tiny little brains. Add icing gel for decoration!

Happy halloween!
