            [title] => SimpleXMLElement Object
                (
                    [0] => 5 Cocktail Recipes for the perfect Christmas Party
                )

            [date] => SimpleXMLElement Object
                (
                    [0] => 2017-12-22 11:00:30
                )

            [content] => <span style="font-weight:400;">Nothing says ‘time to party’ like a gorgeous, colourful cocktail (or three…). Being able to make your own cocktails at home is a fantastic way to impress your guests and give your Christmas or New Year’s Eve party that little something special! Put your mixologist apron on and get ready to DIY some sinfully good cocktails in the comfort of your own home this festive season. </span>
<h3><img class=" aligncenter" src="https://i.giphy.com/media/rY93u9tQbybks/giphy.webp" /><b></b></h3>
<h3><b>1. The Cosmopolitan</b></h3>
 
The drink of choice for the fashion-savvy Carrie Bradshaw (Sex and the City, for the uninitiated), the Cosmo is a delightful mingling of sweet and sour flavours with a lovely, cheerful pink colour. It’s gluten free, and vegetarian and vegan-friendly too. Everybody’s happy, yay!

<img class=" aligncenter" src="https://i.giphy.com/media/5yEeZA1O8mat2/giphy.webp" />

<span style="font-weight:400;">Ingredients (per cocktail)</span>
<ul>
	<li style="list-style-type:none;">
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Ice</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">10 ml lime juice</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">15 ml triple sec</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">45 ml lemon vodka</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">30 ml cranberry juice </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Orange zest OR lime wedge (to decorate glass) </span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight:400;">Method: </span>
<ul>
	<li style="list-style-type:none;">
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Combine the lime juice, triple sec, cranberry juice, and vodka together in a cocktail shaker with ice. Shake until the outside of the shaker is cold, and strain the drink into glasses. </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">For the orange zest garnish, hold a piece of orange zest and carefully heat it over a small flame. The ‘outside’ of the zest should be facing the flame so that the flavours and oils are unlocked; drop the zest into the drink or perch it on the rim of the glass. Alternately, place a lime wedge on the rim of the glass.  </span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><b>2. The Reverse Espresso Martini</b></h3>

<span style="font-weight:400;">Perfect for the coffee fiends among us, this interesting take on the much-loved classic Martini cocktail isn’t just tasty, but promises to perk you and your guests right up. Keep the party going in the best way possible. Cheers to that, ladies and gentlemen.</span>

<img class=" aligncenter" src="https://i.giphy.com/media/l0HlJzBH6Lxdpi8nK/giphy.webp" />

<span style="font-weight:400;">Ingredients (per cocktail) </span>
<ul>
	<li style="list-style-type:none;">
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">50 ml vodka</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">25 ml Baileys </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">30 ml freshly-brewed espresso</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Ice</span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight:400;">Method:</span>
<ul>
	<li style="list-style-type:none;">
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Brew the espresso and freeze it in an ice cube tray.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Mix the vodka and Baileys together with ice in a cocktail shaker. Shake for approximately 1 minute, until the outside of the shaker feels cold.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Place a few espresso ice cubes into each tumbler before straining in the cocktail.  </span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><b>3. The Wintery Whisky Sour</b></h3>
 
<span style="font-weight:400;">The sophisticated whisky sour is a hugely popular bourbon classic and perfect in its tried-and-tested typical form, but for that Christmas twist add a little orange juice for an extra dash of festive zing. Oh, and it’s gluten free!</span>

<img class=" aligncenter" src="https://i.giphy.com/media/3o6ZsUJ44ffpnAW7Dy/giphy.webp" />

<span style="font-weight:400;">Ingredients (for 2 x cocktails)</span>
<ul>
	<li style="list-style-type:none;">
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">50 ml bourbon</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">1 tbsp lemon juice</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">1 tbsp orange juice</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">ice (crushed)</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">1/2 tbsp sugar syrup</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Honey</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Edible gold glitter </span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight:400;">Method:</span>
<ul>
	<li style="list-style-type:none;">
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Use your finger to spread some honey along the rim of two medium-sized tumblers; dip the rim into a plate containing a layer of edible glitter to prepare the glasses.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Fill the glasses with crushed ice and pour bourbon into your cocktail shaker along with the juices and sugar syrup.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Shake it like there’s no tomorrow and strain the cocktail into the glasses.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">(Optional) Serve with an orange slice in the glass itself, and a short straw.  </span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><b>4. The Crimbo Cranberry Margarita</b></h3>
 
<span style="font-weight:400;">This (gluten free) christmassy cocktail isn’t just a pleasure to look at - it’s sweet and lip-smackingly delicious to boot. The contrasting colours and intense flavours are sure to get your guests in the spirit of the season!</span>

<img class=" aligncenter" src="https://i.giphy.com/media/6oB3X3W6MYM3C/giphy.webp" />

<span style="font-weight:400;">Ingredients (for 4 x cocktails)</span>
<ul>
	<li style="list-style-type:none;">
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Ice </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Zest and juice from 1 large orange </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">1 tbsp granulated sugar </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">1 tsp honey </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">200 ml tequila </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">50 ml triple sec </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">1 tbsp coarse sea salt</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">1 lime </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">200 ml cranberry juice </span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight:400;">Method:</span>
<ul>
	<li style="list-style-type:none;">
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Mix together the sugar, salt, and orange zest and lay it out on a saucer.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Get a light layer of honey onto the rim of your Margarita (or Martini) glasses, and dip the rims into the orange zest mixture before letting them chill in the fridge.  </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Use your cocktail shaker to mix together the lime and orange juice, cranberry juice, tequila, triple sec, and ice. Shake until the outside of the shaker is cold.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Strain the cocktail directly into the glasses and voila, you’re done! </span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3><b>5. The Frosty Amaretto Fizz </b></h3>
 
<span style="font-weight:400;">Quick and easy to make, this cocktail is perfect if you find yourself in a bit of a pinch. What better way to kick things off than with something fizzy to welcome your guests with at the door?</span>

<img class=" aligncenter" src="https://i.giphy.com/media/3oriOgivJPodK8Qg9O/giphy.webp" />

<span style="font-weight:400;">Ingredients (for 10 x cocktails)</span>
<ul>
	<li style="list-style-type:none;">
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">150 cl sparkling wine </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Orange zest (in strips)</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">600 ml orange juice </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">400 ml Disaronno</span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight:400;">Method:</span>
<ul>
	<li style="list-style-type:none;">
<ul>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">In a large jug, combine the orange juice, sparkling wine, and Disaronno and mix well before pouring into glasses.</span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Add a strip of orange zest to the glass for extra aesthetic appeal. </span></li>
	<li style="font-weight:400;"><span style="font-weight:400;">Enjoy! </span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
 
<b><i>What your favourite cocktail? Tell us in a comment! </i></b>
 
