            [title] => SimpleXMLElement Object
                (
                    [0] => How to make traditional Maltese kwareżimal
                )

            [date] => SimpleXMLElement Object
                (
                    [0] => 2018-03-26 08:50:42
                )

            [content] => <span lang="en-US">Today’s recipe is a well-loved Maltese classic - </span><span lang="nl-NL"><i>kware</i></span><i>żimal</i><span lang="en-US"><i>! </i></span><span lang="en-US">K</span><span lang="de-DE">ware</span>żimal<span lang="en-US"> is a delicious sweet treat synonymous with Lent, just perfect with a strong cup of tea on a sunny Sunday afternoon. The name ‘</span><span lang="nl-NL">kware</span>żimal<span lang="en-US">’ comes from the Italian word ‘quaresima’, referring to the forty days of Lent during which people would still be able to enjoy these yummy, soft biscuits without breaking their fast. Naughty but nice, right? Get your apron on and roll up your sleeves because we’re about to bake up a stop in here!</span>
[instagram url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BgX-FMzg0GP/?tagged=kwarezimal/ hidecaption=true width=720]
"western" align="LEFT"><span lang="en-US"><b>What you’ll need:</b></span>

<ul>
	<li>
50g margarine
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">400g ground almonds</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">30g chopped, roasted nuts (pistachios or almonds)</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">300g self-raising flour</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">100g wholemeal flour</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">250g caster sugar</span>
</li>
	<li>
2 <span lang="en-US">tbsp orange flower water </span><span lang="it-IT">(ilma </span>żahar)
</li>
	<li>
2 <span lang="en-US">tbsp</span><span lang="nl-NL"> water</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">150g candied peel</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="ru-RU">1 </span><span lang="en-US">tbsp cocoa powder (optional)</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="ru-RU">1 </span><span lang="en-US">tbsp ground cinnamon</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="ru-RU">1 </span><span lang="en-US">tsp mixed spice</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">1 tsp Maltese honey</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">Z</span>est<span lang="en-US"> of 1 lemon</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">Zest of 1 orange</span>
</li>
</ul>
"western" align="LEFT"><span lang="en-US"><b>How to make it:</b></span>

<ol>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">L</span><span lang="de-DE">ine </span><span lang="en-US">a baking tray with parchment and</span> <span lang="en-US">preheat your oven to 180 degrees celsius.</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="de-DE">Sift </span><span lang="en-US">both types of </span><span lang="fr-FR">flour </span><span lang="en-US">together into a bowl,</span> <span lang="en-US">a</span>dd<span lang="en-US">ing the wholemeal</span><span lang="es-ES"> bran </span><span lang="en-US">back into the mixture once you’re done. </span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">Heat the margarine in a saucepan.</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">Next, add the melted margarine and flower water into the flour mixture and mix together well.</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">Add all the remaining ingredients to the flour mixture, </span><span lang="en-US"><b>except </b></span><span lang="en-US">the honey and chopped nuts, and continue to mix.</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">Knead the mixture into a dough. </span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">Divide and mould the dough into rectangular shapes (approximately 2cm thick) and pop them </span>on<span lang="en-US">to the baking tray.</span>
</li>
	<li>
Bake <span lang="en-US">for around 20 minutes, until they turn a nice golden brown.</span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">While still fresh out of the oven</span>, <span lang="en-US">drizzle the biscuits with honey and sprinkle generously with chopped nuts of your choosing. </span>
</li>
	<li>
<span lang="en-US">Once they’ve cooled down a bit</span>,<span lang="en-US"> cut your</span><span lang="nl-NL"> kware</span>ż<span lang="de-DE">imal </span><span lang="en-US">biscuits into chunky slices and serve up with a steaming cup of tea or coffee. Enjoy!</span>
</li>
</ol>
[instagram url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bf3mdaxB3-6/?tagged=kwarezimal/ hidecaption=true width=720]
<span lang="en-US"><i><b>What’s your favourite Maltese treat? Tell us in a comment!</b></i></span>

