            [content] => Have you ever wondered what lies beneath your feet? A network of secret passages lies beneath our beautiful capital. Discover another world when visiting Valletta, Europe's capital of culture 2018. The cisterns are open to the public for the first time until <span class="aBn"><span class="aQJ">1st July as a part of major <a href="https://valletta2018.org/news/valletta-2018-opens-underground-cisterns-as-part-of-major-exhibition/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">exhibition</a> Dal-Baħar Madwarha (The Island is What the Sea Surrounds).</span></span>

The underground cisterns host a sound installation "Who By Fire" by Susan Philipsz, a Scottish artist who won the Turner Prize 2010.

VALLETTA UNDERGROUND CISTERN , Republic Street, Valletta
Exhibition Duration: 25th March - 01 July .
Times: 11am - 7pm. Last Entry at 6:30pm . Closed Mondays.

Adults: €5; Children: €3

Get your ticket here: <a href="http://tickets.valletta2018.org/bookings/Shows.aspx?ProductionId=7" target="_blank" rel="noopener">http://tickets.valletta2018.org</a>

[wpvideo 7l9uZCmg]

Planning a trip to Malta? <a href="http://shortletsmalta.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shortletsmalta.com</a> is a perfect place to find a flat for rent in Malta.<strong> </strong>Discover and enjoy Malta and all its history.
