            [blog_content] => If you’ve been following our blog recently, you might have noticed that we’re really putting an effort into providing different ways of immersing yourself in the beauty that is our natural Maltese landscape. Malta has such an endless supply of nature that we can’t imagine anyone getting tired of it, but it’s precisely because Malta’s beauty is so tireless that finding new ways of exploring it is the ultimate way of appreciating it.

Kayaking is just one of the ways that you can become one with the archipelago, but what a way it is.

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2157" src="https://shortletsmalta.files.wordpress.com/2017/04/kayak-1.gif" alt="kayak 1.gif" width="480" height="360" />

Of course, if you want to travel around Malta’s sea, the options are practically limitless. Why opt for a kayak? We like to think of kayaking as a best-of-all-worlds kind of vessel. By that we mean that you get all the serenity that comes with being on a boat (perhaps even more so because there are no noisy engines) and you also get a serious workout in the process, especially with regard to your upper body. We know that exercise is not on everyone’s minds when it comes to these things, but it’s always worth mentioning!

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2158" src="https://shortletsmalta.files.wordpress.com/2017/04/kayak-2.gif" alt="kayak 2.gif" width="350" height="192" />

Kayaking is also great for another reason that is definitely underrated, which is that kayaks are better for the fish in the sea than most other kinds of sea vessels. Because kayaks are so stealthy and smooth in design, the fish will not even notice your presence. We do understand that some people do opt to go fishing on kayaks, but that’s another (umm) kettle of fish entirely.

Have we convinced you that kayaking is a wonderful activity to try in Malta? Great! The question that remains is how to get started. Fortunately, the answer is even easier than the question! All you have to do is make a booking through Fun Malta!

Fun Malta is a booking agent for MC Adventure, a group of adventure-driven professionals that can organise kayaking activities you’ll never forget. Perfect for small or large groups, there are a multitude of options available when looking into your next kayaking trip. You can even opt for a half-day activity or a full-day one!

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2159" src="https://shortletsmalta.files.wordpress.com/2017/04/kayak-3.gif" alt="kayak 3.gif" width="480" height="360" />

For the (understandably) safety-conscious: thanks to the experts at MC Adventure accompanying you every step of the way, there’s no need for worry as you’ll get all the help you need. That means beginners are more than welcome to join in on the fun.

The best part of course is that there are multiple spots that are suitable for kayaking and this is reflected in the range of tours on offer. One of the most popular ones include a kayaking adventure to Comino, which is full of natural arches and caves. Another takes you to the delightfully underrated area of Selmun Bay and the St Paul’s Islands (also known as Selmunett)!

For more information, including prices, and to make a direct booking, visit <a href="http://www.funmalta.com/kayaking">www.funmalta.com/kayaking</a>. Enjoy your kayaking adventure!
