            [blog_content] => <span lang="en-US">Date night is always special. It doesn</span>’<span lang="en-US">t matter if you</span>’<span lang="en-US">ve been together for two weeks, two decades, or are anxiously stepping out for your first date - choosing the right setting for your romantic rendezvous is an absolute must. Now Malta might be small in size, but make no mistake - this little island is big on food! Without further ado, here are 5 restaurants in Malta to get you started on the way your perfect date.</span>

<h2 class="western">1. Rebekah’s, Mellieħa</h2>
<span lang="en-US">Head up to the picturesque north of Malta and enjoy an evening of first-class Mediterranean cuisine and stellar service at Rebekah</span>’<span lang="en-US">s, a restaurant brimming with rustic local charm. For that extra hint of magic, try to get a table outside, in the courtyard, to make the most of those warm summer nights.</span>
<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2440" src="https://shortletsmalta.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/credit_rebekahs_facebook.png" alt="Credit_Rebekahs_Facebook" width="783" height="782" />


<h2 class="western"><span lang="it-IT">2. Trattoria Da Pippo, Valletta</span></h2>
<span lang="en-US">Nestled in one of Valletta</span>’<span lang="en-US">s many side streets, you</span>’<span lang="en-US">ll find the brightly-coloured entrance to Trattoria da Pippo, a bustling, cheerful restaurant serving up some of the freshest Italian food on the island. This gem of a restaurant is perfect for a daytime date! </span>
https://www.instagram.com/p/BS8EnebhU0y/?taken-at=279349688


<h2 class="western"><span lang="it-IT">3. Del Borgo, Birgu</span></h2>
<span lang="en-US">This wine bar and restaurant is located in typically-Maltese Birgu (one of the historic Three Cities), hidden away in one of its many narrow streets. Just minutes away from the waterfront, the ambience at Del Borgo is perfect for that quiet, intimate night out - and the candlelight is a pretty nice touch, too. </span>
https://www.instagram.com/p/BUhoMCbjCgG/?taken-at=181295


<h2 class="western">4. Terrone, Marsaxlokk</h2>
<span lang="en-US">The south of Malta is simply idyllic, especially during the summer months. Terrone is an adorable restaurant right by the sea in Marsaxlokk, a sleepy fishing village with some of the most incredible seafood on offer. </span>
https://www.instagram.com/p/BUcedK0hG5U/?taken-by=ljuanax


<h2 class="western"></h2>
<h2 class="western"></h2>
<h2 class="western">5. <span lang="en-US">Cellini Wine Bar</span>, <span lang="en-US">Naxxar</span></h2>
<span lang="en-US">For a fantastic night out away from the hustle and bustle of St. Julian</span>’<span lang="en-US">s and Sliema, had over to Cellini in Naxxar, right next to the impressive parish church, and indulge in some wine and a cheeky platter with your someone special. </span>
 <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2444" src="https://shortletsmalta.files.wordpress.com/2017/05/credit_cellini_wine_bar.png" alt="Credit_Cellini_Wine_Bar.png" width="955" height="715" />

<h2 class="western"></h2>
