                    [0] => 5 Summertime Activities to Keep you Cool in Malta
                )

            [blog_date] => SimpleXMLElement Object
                (
                    [0] => 2017-07-28 10:00:12
                )

            [blog_content] => <span lang="en-US">It’s no secret - summer in the Mediterranean is pretty amazing. What's not to love? The long, sun-drenched days melt away into fiery sunsets and cool yet lively nights, and time spent relaxing isn’t just accepted, but actively encouraged by the locals. So what’s the best way to cool down when you’re visiting our gem of an island this summer? Here are just a few ideas to get things started!</span>

<h3 align="LEFT"><span lang="en-US"><b>1 | <a href="https://www.funmalta.com/snorkeling" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Snorkeling</a> and <a href="https://www.funmalta.com/scuba-diving" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Scuba Diving</a></b></span></h3>
<span lang="en-US">When you’re surrounded by gentle blue waves as far as the eye can see, it’s basically </span><span lang="en-US"><i>impossible </i></span><span lang="en-US"> to resist going for a dip. Snorkeling or scuba diving are two great ways to keep cool while you get up close and personal with the real ‘locals’ underwater. Grab your goggles and a set of flippers and get ready to be immersed in a cyan-coloured world so magical, you’l forget you live on land.</span>
https://www.instagram.com/p/BJhnEOFg_sI/?taken-by=maltaphotography
<h3 align="LEFT"><span lang="en-US"><b>2 | <a href="https://www.funmalta.com/sup-yoga" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SUP Yoga</a></b></span></h3>
<span lang="en-US">Revitalise your mind and body with a spot of yoga - but wit ha twist! SUP Yoga is ‘stand up paddle’ yoga, done on a surf board in calm waters. Even if your balance is on point, you might still find yourself ‘falling’ into that tempting blue sea to cool down after all that hard work.</span>
https://www.instagram.com/p/BW8GxJ6BAR3/?tagged=supyoga
<h3 align="LEFT"><span lang="en-US"><b>3 | <a href="https://www.funmalta.com/comino-sunset-cruise" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Comino at Sunset</a></b></span></h3>
<span lang="en-US">Comino is a piece of paradise right on our doorstep - so why not grab a few friends and spend the day cruising around over there? For that extra bit of Maltese magic, make sure you’re there to see the sun set over the horizon.</span>
https://www.instagram.com/p/BW7ZMEGB4tK/?tagged=malta
<h3 align="LEFT"><span lang="en-US"><b>4 | <a href="https://www.funmalta.com/watersports" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wild Watersports</a></b></span></h3>
<span lang="en-US">If you want something with a bit more adrenaline involved, we’ve got you covered. Jet skiing, intense sofa rides, wake boarding, banana boating, canning - take your pick!</span>
https://www.instagram.com/p/YDAXBCgUrL/?tagged=jetskimalta
<h3 align="LEFT"><span lang="en-US"><b>5 | <a href="https://www.funmalta.com/round-malta-cruise" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cruise around Malta</a></b></span></h3>
<span lang="en-US">Get away from the hustle and bustle of island life and escape to the sea on a tour around Malta! From awe-inspiring cliffs and beautiful bays to a stunning coastline and swimming in crystal-blue seas, you won’t be forgetting about this any time soon.</span>
https://www.instagram.com/p/BInWwt9AzPV/?taken-by=maltaphotographyamp;hl=en
