            [blog_content] => Malta - the small island with a very big personality indeed. One of the things we love most about our three sun-drenched pieces of Mediterranean paradise is this: no matter how many times you’ve visited, or how long you have lived here, there is always something new to discover. From technicolour sunsets that need no filter, to <a href="https://www.funmalta.com/trekking"><span style="color:#1155cc;"><u>scenic treks</u></span></a> through the rugged Maltese countryside, secret, long-forgotten caves to explore and beyond, there’s no end to the things you’ll see here. But today, let’s take a look at just 10 #Malta snaps that’ will make you fall in love with Malta - for the first time or all over again.
<strong>10. Fabulous fireworks</strong>

https://www.instagram.com/p/BThlV9nl-UY/?tagged=funmalta

<strong>9. The streets of Valletta</strong>

https://www.instagram.com/p/Bh38qW9BEwb/?tagged=malta

<strong>8. Popeye Village looking cute</strong>

https://www.instagram.com/p/BSbu4HXhh9h/?taken-by=arguablykelly

<strong>7. Picture-perfect Blue Lagoon</strong>

https://www.instagram.com/p/Bh3_S5TFbCt/?tagged=malta

<strong>6. This hauntingly-beautiful shipwreck</strong>

https://www.instagram.com/p/Bh33fedAyye/?tagged=malta

<strong>5. Sunset in the fishing village of Marsaxlokk</strong>

https://www.instagram.com/p/Bh33AZ5jjwC/?tagged=malta

<strong>4. Lazy days spent in Ta’ Qali</strong>

https://www.instagram.com/p/Bh3zBiIHXXr/?tagged=malta

<strong>3. A touch of drama at the Manoel Theatre</strong>

https://www.instagram.com/p/Bh3vdeOHjxS/?tagged=malta

