            [blog_content] => <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-4448" src="https://shortletsmalta.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/972009_559928907383030_701372950_n.jpg" alt="972009_559928907383030_701372950_n" width="720" height="540" />

<strong>Ingredients</strong>

1 loaf of country life gluten free bread
4 cups of milk
Zest of 1 orange
1/2 cup fruit meadly
4 tablespoons brown sugar
3 tablespoons cocoa powder
100gms of 85% dark chocolate
1/2 cup glass cherries
2 eggs

<strong>Method</strong>
<ul>
	<li>Breakup the bread into small pieces</li>
	<li>Place in a bowl with milk and soak for 30 - 60 minutes</li>
	<li>Combine rest of ingredients and mix well pour into a slice tray</li>
	<li>Decorate with almonds and cherries</li>
	<li>Bake in a fan forced oven at 180°C for 40 minutes</li>
</ul>
Happy Cooking!
