            [blog_content] => Muffins lovers? This recipe is for you!

<strong>Ingredients</strong>
<ul>
	<li>2 cups flour</li>
	<li>2 teaspoons baking powder</li>
	<li>1/2 teaspoon bicarbonate of soda</li>
	<li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
	<li>1 cup yogurt</li>
	<li>1/4 cup olive oil and 2 eggs</li>
	<li>1 teaspoon turmeric</li>
	<li>Some dried thyme</li>
	<li>Parsley</li>
	<li>Finely chopped tomatoes</li>
	<li>Turkey ham</li>
	<li>Chopped cheese</li>
	<li>Grated and a crushed garlic clove</li>
</ul>
<strong>Method</strong>
<ul>
	<li >In a bowl: sift 2 cups flour, 2 teaspoons baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon bicarbonate of soda,1/2 teaspoon salt,1 cup yogurt,1/4 cup olive oil and 2 eggs.</li>
	<li >This is the basic recipe to it you can then add your favorite ingredients.</li>
	<li >Add 1 teaspoon turmeric, some dried thyme, parsley, finely chopped tomatoes, turkey ham, chopped cheese and grated and a crushed garlic clove. You can add dried tomatoes, olives, chopped cooked chicken or other kind of meat, zucchini, tuna....just use your imagination.</li>
	<li >Bake in a preheated 180°C oven for about 20 minutes. I made 8 large muffins. These are ideal for picnics, breakfast, packed lunches, parties etc.</li>
</ul>
Enjoy!
