            [blog_content] => <h3><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-4532" src="https://shortletsmalta.files.wordpress.com/2018/05/accras_de_morue_recadre.jpg" alt="accras_de_morue_recadre" width="573" height="322" /></h3>
<h3></h3>
<h3>Ingredients</h3>
<ul>
	<li>500g salt cod</li>
	<li>50g plain flour</li>
	<li>1tsp baking power</li>
	<li>Pinch of salt</li>
	<li>Lemon Juice</li>
	<li>2 cloves of garlic, crushed</li>
</ul>
<h3>Method</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Soak the cod in cold water overnight, discard and replace the water sever times (soak during the day so you don't have to wake up at night :) ) Make the batter and add the lemon juice.</li>
	<li>Boil the fish until tender, cut into strips when cold and stir into the batter.</li>
	<li>Deep Fry as small balls until golden brown.</li>
	<li>Drain and serve hot.</li>
</ul>
Enjoy!
