            [blog_content] => Birgu, also known as ‘Città Vittoriosa’ is an old fortified city facing Valletta, and it’s the place where the Knights of St. John first settled. Not only is this small city bursting with history, architecture, and museums but it also has a beautiful marina with cafes and restaurants along the waterfront. Whether visiting during the day or in the evening, Birgu is definitely worth it.


[wpvideo KZyT32pU]
If you are planning a trip to the Maltese Islands in Autumn 2018, then you are in for a cultural treat! Birgufest 2018 is a celebration of culture and art, which will be taking place in Birgu . Check the details of the festival here: <a href="https://www.visitmalta.com/en/event-details/2018-10/birgufest-11031" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.visitmalta.com/birgufest</a>


<img class=" aligncenter" title="Birgufest 2018" src="https://www.visitmalta.com/en/event-details/2018-10/file.aspx?f=30768" alt="Birgufest 2018" />
